We want to maximize
 \begin {align*} \mathcal {L}(\theta ) &= \mathbb {E}_{x \sim  p_X, y \sim  p_Y}\Big [\log \sigma (f_{\theta }(x)) + \log (1-\sigma (f_{\theta }(y)))\Big ] \\ &= \int  \log \sigma (f_{\theta }(x)) P_X(x) + \int  \log (1-\sigma (f_{\theta }(y))) P_Y(y) \\ &= \int  \log \sigma (f_{\theta }(z)) P_X(z) + \log (1-\sigma (f_{\theta }(z))) P_Y(z)     \end {align*}     
Since we are maximizing f(s), we can just maximize the integrand i.e.
   \begin {align*}         \frac {\mathrm {d}}{\mathrm {d}f(z)} \Big [\log \sigma (f_{\theta }(z)) P_X(z) + \log (1-\sigma (f_{\theta }(z))) P_Y(z)\Big ] = 0       \end {align*}     
Solving,
         \begin {align*}           P_X(z)\big (1 - \sigma (f(z))\big ) - P_Y(z)\sigma (f(z)) = 0 &\iff  \sigma (f(z)) = \frac {P_X(z)}{P_X(z) + P_Y(z)} \\           &\iff  f(z) = \log \left (\frac {P_X(z)}{P_Y(z)}\right )         \end {align*}
